https://leetcode.com/problems/timeout-cancellation/submissions/1981871076

Call function immediately, repeat using setInterval, and stop using clearInterval.

Code-

var cancellable = function(fn, args, t) {
    const timerId = setTimeout(() => {
        fn(...args);
    }, t);

    return function cancelFn() {
        clearTimeout(timerId);
    };
};

--------------------------------------------------

Key Points-
First call is immediate (manual call)
setInterval handles repeated execution
clearInterval stops execution
Must store interval ID


